TY  - JOUR
AU  - Doraszelski, Ulrich
AU  - Jaumandreu, Jordi
T1  - R&amp;D and Productivity: Estimating Endogenous Productivity
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdt011
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 80
IS  - 4
SP  - 1338
EP  - 1383
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We develop a model of endogenous productivity change to examine the impact of the investment in knowledge on the productivity of firms. Our dynamic investment model extends the tradition of the knowledge capital model of Griliches (1979) that has remained a cornerstone of the productivity literature. Rather than constructing a stock of knowledge capital from a firm's observed R&amp;D expenditures, we consider productivity to be unobservable to the econometrician. Our approach accounts for uncertainty, non-linearity, and heterogeneity across firms in the link between R&amp;D and productivity. We also derive a novel estimator for production functions in this setting. Using an unbalanced panel of more than 1800 Spanish manufacturing firms in nine industries during the 1990s, we provide evidence of non-linearities as well as economically significant uncertainties in the R&amp;D process. R&amp;D expenditures play a key role in determining the differences in productivity across firms and the evolution of firm-level productivity over time.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdt011
ER  - 



